page.title: 07Ecology, Rossall
page.content: A bleak, wind swept coast with no trees and little other vegetation. The floods of 1977 led to the artificial fixing of the sand dune behind the sea wall with a plastic mesh. Plants colonizing the dune (about 4m high) include; Honkenya peploides, Eryngium maritimum, Crambe maritima, Ammophila arenaria, Tripleurospermum maritiamum, Rumex crispus, Rumex ostusifolius, Elymus arenarius, Geranium molle, Carduus nutans, Plantago lanceolata, Achillea millefolium, Potentilla tabernaemontani, Ammoracia rusticana.
